Surgical approach to insulinomas. Assessing the need for preoperative localization. The purpose of this study was to examine our experience with the diagnosis, surgical approach, and outcomes of surgery for organic hyperinsulinemia in the era of transhepatic venous sampling. During the period from 1978 to 1991, 50 patients were evaluated and treated for hyperinsulinemia at the University of Michigan Medical Center, all of whom underwent preoperative localization. Forty-one patients (82%) had solitary, benign tumors four (8%) had either multiple tumors or islet cell dysplasia